{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:09.073969+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's what I found from the repository's documentation:\n\n---\n\n## Non-Docker Setup Path\n\nThe `README.md` contains a dedicated section titled **\"Installation without Docker\"**. The documented workflow is:\n\n1. **Install Poetry** (the only prerequisite for non-Docker development).\n2. **Create a virtual environment** with all project dependencies by running:\n   ```bash\n   poetry install\n   ```\n   at the root of the project.\n3. **Set the database connection string environment variable** and start the server:\n   ```bash\n   export DB_STRING=sqlite:///test.db/\n   poetry run alembic upgrade head && poetry run uvicorn api.main:app --port 5000 --reload\n   ```\n   - `alembic upgrade head` applies all pending database migrations.\n   - `uvicorn api.main:app` starts the FastAPI app with hot-reload on port 5000.\n\nThe application is then available at `http://localhost:5000/docs`.\n\n---\n\n## Required Database Connection String Variable\n\nThe environment variable that must be set is:\n\n> **`DB_STRING`**\n\nThe README example sets it to `sqlite:///test.db/`, which points Alembic/Uvicorn at a local SQLite database file (`test.db`). This is distinct from the placeholder `sqlalchemy.url` found in `alembic.ini` (which is just a generic default `driver://user:pass@localhost/dbname`); the **runtime override** comes from the `DB_STRING` environment variable.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 336, "prompt_tokens": 6546, "total_tokens": 6882, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4032, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.001